+# D.U.H. Documentation
+
+**D.U.H.** (D.U.H. is a Universal Harness) is an open-source, provider-agnostic
+AI coding agent. The codebase organizes itself around a minimal agentic kernel
+that knows nothing about which LLM it talks to, how tools execute, how output
+gets rendered, or how conversations persist — every such concern is a **port**
+(a runtime-checkable Protocol in `duh/ports/`) that concrete **adapters**
+satisfy. The documents below describe the same codebase from three different
+heights.
+
+## [ARCHITECTURE.md](./ARCHITECTURE.md)
+
+The architect's view: module layout, component diagram, how a request flows
+from `duh -p "..."` through CLI parsing, system-prompt construction, the
+`Engine` session wrapper, the `query()` loop, provider adapters, tool
+executors, and back to a rendered stream. Covers the extension points you'd
+touch to add a provider, tool, or slash command; the security architecture
+(taint propagation via `UntrustedStr`, HMAC confirmation tokens, PEP 578
+audit bridge, platform sandboxing); the asyncio-based concurrency model;
+and the tradeoffs the design deliberately accepts.
+
+## [TUTORIAL.md](./TUTORIAL.md)
+
+The practitioner's view: a hands-on walkthrough from first install to a
+working custom tool, using only APIs that exist in this checkout. You'll
+install the package, verify the stub provider works offline, instantiate an
+`Engine` against it, then build a `WordCountTool` end-to-end — JSON Schema,
+async `call()`, registration with `NativeExecutor`, an `AutoApprover`,
+wiring it all into `Deps`, and observing tool-use events streaming from
+`engine.run()`. Every code block is runnable against commit `645d91a`.
+
+## [API.md](./API.md)
+
+The reference: every public class, function, protocol, and constant
+exported from `duh/kernel/` and `duh/ports/`. Each entry lists the exact
+signature as it appears in source, the parameter and return types, the
+exceptions raised, and one short example. Use this when you want to know
+what `Engine.run()` actually yields, what fields `Deps` carries, what
+`UntrustedStr.__add__` does to taint, or which methods a `MemoryStore`
+implementation must provide.
